node.title: Victoria records 860 new COVID-19 cases and five deaths
node.description: There are now 17,518 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 416 people have died in the state during the current Delta outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 860\u00a0new COVID-19 cases and five\u00a0deaths.", "There are now 17,518\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 416\u00a0people have died in the state during the current Delta outbreak.", "There are 378\u00a0people in hospital with the virus, of whom 78\u00a0are in intensive care and 48\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The health department said a further 71\u00a0people are\u00a0in intensive care, but their COVID-19 infections are no longer considered active.", "The new cases were detected from 48,104\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 5,030\u00a0doses of vaccine administered at state-run sites yesterday, as well as more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "More to come.", "", "
